article.description:
Betty Lennox scored a season-high 24 points as the
Miami Sol won their fourth straight game, beating the Orlando Miracle 70-56 Saturday night.
article.headline: Miami tops Orlando for fourth straight win
article.linkText: Lennox scores 24 as Sol roll into All-Star break
article.story:
MIAMI (AP) -- Betty Lennox scored a season-high 24 points as the
Miami Sol won their fourth straight game, beating the Orlando
Miracle 70-56 Saturday night.

	   The Sol got a boost from Lennox, a reserve guard who connected
on 7 of 14 shots -- including 3-for-3 from three-point range --
before leaving with 2:46 remaining because of a left thigh bruise.

	   Lennox doesn't expect to miss any more time because of the
injury.

	   The Miracle backed off and gave Lennox open looks, and she made
them pay with her best game of the season.

	   ''I came out ready to play,'' Lennox said. ''I have to give my
teammates credit for finding me. Plus, they didn't really guard me
close, so I took what the defense gave me.''

	   Lennox's previous high was 19 points, which she reached twice
this season.

	   ''That's what she is capable of,'' Miami coach Ron Rothstein
said. ''When she takes good shots, she knows how to score.''

	   Miami (9-10) went into the All-Star break having won seven of
eight. Orlando (9-9) fell to .500 after losing its third game in a
row and fourth in six games.

	   The teams split two close games -- decided by four points or
fewer -- earlier this season, each winning on the other's home
court.

	   Sheri Sam, who will represent Miami in the All-Star Game, scored
15 points and added six rebounds.

	   All-Star Shannon Johnson led Orlando with 15 points and Wendy
Palmer added 13. The Miracle committed 19 turnovers and shot 38
percent.

	   ''Betty had a huge first half and kept them in the game,''
Orlando coach Dee Brown said. ''In the second half we contained her
pretty well, but other players, like Sheri, stepped up and came up
big.

	   ''It's the All-Star break, and it comes at a good time for us.
We need a break to get away from things for a little bit and come
back refreshed for the second half of the season.''
